b'Tom (not his real name) did not have the best start in life. His father was abusive, and one of his sisters had leukaemia. These challenging family circumstances led Tom\xe2\x80\x99s mother into depression. She was later deemed unfit to take care of her children. One day, a family service centre connected the then 12-year old Tom with a CapitaLand employee Edward (not his real name) through a programme for underprivileged children supported by CapitaLand\xe2\x80\x99s philanthropic arm CapitaLand Hope Foundation. 

Their first meeting marked the beginning of a lasting connection \xe2\x80\x93 seven years and counting. Edward introduced Tom to activities like ice skating, table tennis, and cycling. They gradually built an emotional bond as they spent more time together. Tom would confide in Edward and Edward would provide support to Tom as best as he could.  Watch: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zaTz1oPRLos&feature=youtu.be

CapitaLand is a strong advocate of staff volunteerism, believing that it is not only a meaningful way to contribute to the community but also further multiplies its giving effort as well as provides staff a sense of purpose by showing care for the underprivileged. More: https://www.capitaland.com/volunteerism

#CapitaLand #CapitaLandHopeFoundation #SGUnited #SingaporeTogether #Philanthropy #CSR #Volunteerism #ChampionofGood #OrganisationOfGood #CompanyofGood'

b'Mr Ameerali Jumabhoy was a visionary leader who ignited the evolution of the serviced residence industry with the opening of the first international-class serviced residence in Asia Pacific, The Ascott Singapore, in 1984.
\xc2\xa0
The Ascott brand, and the distinctive logo he created, has grown from a single building in Singapore to a global brand with more than 760 properties in over 30 countries. Ascott remains close to the hearts of many, and Mr Jumabhoy\xe2\x80\x99s legacy will continue to touch the lives of tens of thousands of people around the world.
\xc2\xa0
Our thoughts are with the Jumabhoy family.'

b'What\xe2\x80\x99s next for CapitaLand in the next 20 years? As we mark CapitaLand\xe2\x80\x99s 20th anniversary this month, we asked 20 of our stakeholders, including media editors and the public, to pose questions to our Group CEO, Mr Lee Chee Koon. Ranging from his leadership philosophy to lessons learnt from COVID-19 and his career advice for the next-gen workforce, these questions helped in shaping \xe2\x80\x9cThe Next 20\xe2\x80\x9d, a CapitaLand framework built on 3 core tenets of :people_holding_hands:People, :seedling:Sustainability and :laptop_computer:Digitalisation, that supports our vision of becoming a global real estate player. :globe_showing_Americas:

b'Five years in a row! The Ascott Limited (Ascott) has been recognised as the \xe2\x80\x98Leading Serviced Apartment Brand\xe2\x80\x99 at this year\xe2\x80\x99s World Travel Awards for Asia and Europe. Ascott has held the title since 2016.
.
Ascott emerged the biggest winner among the serviced residence players at the prestigious World Travel Awards for Asia and Europe with 18 accolades in total. Ascott also bagged the \xe2\x80\x98Leading Serviced Apartment Brand\xe2\x80\x99 award in Singapore, Hong Kong, Malaysia, Philippines and Vietnam. Voted by tourism professionals and business and leisure travellers worldwide, winners of the annual World Travel Awards are globally recognised as hallmarks of industry excellence.
.
Mr Alfred Ong, Ascott\xe2\x80\x99s Head for Global Operations, said: \xe2\x80\x9cBeing recognised again as the top serviced apartment brand in Asia and Europe is an affirmation of the quality and excellence that Ascott offers to our guests and partners.\xe2\x80\x9d
Props to the Ascott team for their dedication to service excellence.
.

b'"Nothing is art if it does not come from nature." - Antoni Gaudi. 

Inspired by the mountains and rivers in the Sichuan Province, CapitaMall Tianfu in Chengdu pays tribute to the city's natural heritage with an expert blend of aluminium and glass to create rock-like formations that shimmer under the sunlight.

The eight-storey CapitaMall Tianfu was opened in 2014 and had been recognised for its innovative retail and leisure concept. Designed by @woha_architects, the mall continues to capture the imagination of many in Chengdu.

b'Ascott has achieved a #record high signing of over 5,600 units in #China to date despite #COVID19. This is a 60% year-on-year growth in units in China. Recovering strongly in China, #Ascott has: 

:up_arrow_selector: Signed more than 2,100 units across 12 properties over the last 3 months
:up_arrow_selector: Reached close to 95% of pre-COVID-19 levels for revenue of operating properties in Sep 2020
:up_arrow_selector: Achieved an average occupancy rate of over 86% for properties in tier one cities in Sep 2020

Globally, Ascott has sealed new contracts for more than 3,700 units across 22 properties; about 60% are from China and the rest are in various markets including #Austria and #Indonesia.

Mr Kevin Goh, CapitaLand\xe2\x80\x99s Chief Executive Officer for Lodging and Ascott\xe2\x80\x99s Chief Executive Officer, said: \xe2\x80\x9cThe COVID-19 pandemic has brought the resilience and flexibility of Ascott\xe2\x80\x99s business model to the fore. In 2020, we have signed more than 9,300 units in 48 properties worldwide while expanding in China at a record rate. We are also planting new flags in markets such as Austria and Indonesia, offering our guests a wider network of Ascott properties.\xe2\x80\x9d

b'With COVID-19, face masks:face_with_medical_mask: have become an integral part of our lives. However, wearing face masks can be challenging for children and youths with special needs. To encourage these children and youths to embrace mask-wearing and teach them how to store their masks properly, our philanthropic arm CapitaLand Hope Foundation, came up with an idea to make mask pouches. 

Through #CareKitWithLove initiative, we hope to make 8,000 mask pouches with the help of the community:flexed_biceps:. In June 2020, we partnered with @yellowribbonsg to make over 1,400 mask pouches for students with special needs from @rainbowcentresingapore. CapitaLand staff volunteers and Rainbow Centre staff co-designed the mask pouch to encourage the students to wear face masks and maintain proper hygiene. Staff volunteers also curated a guide to help teachers explain the use of the mask pouch and demonstrated to the students how to personalise the pouch through virtual art sessions. 

Find out more in our IG story.
